    "path = \"A:\\RWTH Aachen\\Computational intelligence\\Project 1\\Data\\Smartphone1\\subject10_normal01\\Accelerometer.csv\"\n",
    "time, x, y, z = np.loadtxt(path, delimiter=',', unpack = True,skiprows=1)\n",
    "def check(k):\n",
    "    if \"Gyroscope\" in path :\n",
    "        p = np.rad2deg(k)\n",
    "    elif \"Accelerometer\" in path :\n",
    "        p = k;\n",
    "    return p\n",
    "def gravity(g):\n",
    "    if \"Gyroscope\" in path :\n",
    "        g = g\n",
    "    elif \"Accelerometer\" in path :\n",
    "        g = g-9.8;\n",
    "    return g\n",
    "def trainval():\n",
    "    if \"normal\" in path:\n",
    "        value = 0;\n",
    "    elif \"impaired\" in path :\n",
    "        value = 1;\n",
    "    return value\n",
    "def plotting(time,x,y,z):\n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 1, 1)\n",
    "    plt.plot(time,check(x),color = \"blue\", label = \"xaxis\")\n",
    "    plt.title('A tale of 3 subplots')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('X acceleration')\n",
    "    y = y-9.8\n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 1, 2)\n",
    "    plt.plot(time,check(y),color = \"red\", label = \"yaxis\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('time (s)')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Y acceleration')\n",
    "    \n",
    "    plt.subplot(3, 1, 3)\n",
    "    plt.plot(time, check(z),color = \"yellow\", label = \"zaxis\")\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('time (s)')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('Z acceleration')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "plotting(time,x,y,z)    "
   ]

    "def resample_axis(time,axis):\n",
    "    time_n = time[2]-time[1]\n",
    "    freq = 1/time_n\n",
    "    if freq > 200: \n",
    "        f = signal.resample(axis,2*axis.size)\n",
    "    elif freq < 200 and freq > 120:\n",
    "        f = signal.resample(axis,axis.size)\n",
    "    tre = np.linspace (0,100,len(f),endpoint = False)\n",
    "    plt.plot(time, np.rad2deg(x),'b',tre,np.rad2deg(f),'or')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('time')\n",
    "    plt.ylabel('axis')\n",
    "    plt.legend(['data', 'resampled'], loc='best')\n",
    "    plt.show()\n",
    "    return tre,f\n",
    "tre,xre=resample_axis(time,x)\n",
    "tre,yre=resample_axis(time,y)\n",
    "tre,zre=resample_axis(time,z)"
   ]

    "import numpy as np\n",
    "from scipy.signal import butter, lfilter, freqz, filtfilt\n",
    "from matplotlib import pyplot as plt\n",
    "\n",
    "\n",
    "def butter_lowpass(cutoff, fs, order=5):\n",
    "    nyq = 0.5 * fs\n",
    "    normal_cutoff = cutoff / nyq\n",
    "    b, a = butter(order, normal_cutoff, btype='low', analog=False)\n",
    "    return b, a\n",
    "\n",
    "def butter_lowpass_filter(data, cutoff, fs, order=5):\n",
    "    b, a = butter_lowpass(cutoff, fs, order=order)\n",
    "    y = filtfilt(b, a, data)\n",
    "    return y\n",
    "\n",
    "def resampling(t, axis):\n",
    "    # Filter requirements.\n",
    "    order = 6\n",
    "    fs = 100.0       # sample rate, Hz\n",
    "    cutoff = 10  # desired cutoff frequency of the filter, Hz\n",
    "    \n",
    "    # Get the filter coefficients so we can check its frequency response.\n",
    "    b, a = butter_lowpass(cutoff, fs, order)\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Demonstrate the use of the filter.\n",
    "    # First make some data to be filtered.\n",
    "    #T = len(time)            # seconds\n",
    "    #n = int(T * fs)     # total number of samples\n",
    "    #t = np.linspace(0, T, n, endpoint=False)\n",
    "    t = t\n",
    "    # \"Noisy\" data.  We want to recover the 1.2 Hz signal from this.\n",
    "    data = axis\n",
    "\n",
    "    # Filter the data, and plot both the original and filtered signals.\n",
    "    y = butter_lowpass_filter(data, cutoff, fs, order)\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.subplot(2, 1, 2)\n",
    "    plt.plot(t, data, 'b.-', label='data')\n",
    "    plt.plot(t, y, 'g', linewidth=2, label='filtered data')\n",
    "    plt.xlabel('Time [sec]')\n",
    "    plt.grid()\n",
    "    plt.legend()\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.subplots_adjust(hspace=.35)\n",
    "    plt.show()"
   ]
  },
